Place a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} on top rack (for 4 servings, 2 lightly oiled
baking sheets, on top and middle racks) and preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); thinly slice crosswise
into half-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add @bacon{4%oz} and cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning
too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a
#paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan. Once cool enough to handle, roughly
chop.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2.5%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add zucchini and cook, stirring, until lightly browned and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

> Use pan used for bacon here.

While zucchini cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomatoes, garlic, and a drizzle
of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second small bowl, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, half the lemon zest,
½ tsp olive oil (1 tsp for 4 servings), and lemon juice to taste. Season with
salt and pepper.

Carefully place @flatbreads{2} on prepared sheet (divide between both prepared
sheets for 4 servings). Evenly spread flatbreads with lemon ricotta. Top with
zucchini and tomatoes, cut sides up.

Bake on top rack (top and middle racks for 4) until flatbreads are golden brown,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Top flatbreads with chopped bacon along with veggies.

Meanwhile, pick @green herb blend{1}(parsley leaves picked from stems; roughly
chopped) and @?chives{}(minced).

Once flatbreads are done, top with parsley, chives, and remaining lemon zest.
Drizzle with @honey{2%teaspoon}, then slice into pieces.

Divide between plates and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.